# Build directories
build/
build-*/
cmake-build-*/

# CMake
CMakeCache.txt
CMakeFiles/
cmake_install.cmake
CTestTestfile.cmake
Testing/
compile_commands.json

# Compiled objects / binaries
*.o
*.obj
*.a
*.so
*.exe
*.out

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/

# LaTeX intermediates only. The compiled report/main.pdf IS committed, on
# purpose: the build spec asks for the repository to be browsable with zero
# setup and no MPI, and a reader landing on GitHub should be able to open the
# finished report and see the figures without cloning, installing a TeX
# distribution, or having MPI hardware. Regenerate it with `make report`.
report/*.aux
report/*.log
report/*.out
report/*.toc
report/*.bbl
report/*.blg
report/*.fls
report/*.fdb_latexmk
report/*.synctex.gz
report/sections/*.aux
report/*.bcf
report/*.run.xml

# Figures and tables are build products of analysis/run_full_analysis.py, but
# the .pdf figures and .tex tables ARE committed so the report renders and the
# results are visible on GitHub without running the pipeline. The .png rasters
# are intermediates used only to refresh docs/assets/busbw_preview.png, so they
# stay ignored.
report/figures/*.png

# OS cruft
.DS_Store

# Local/cluster sweep output (ad hoc, regenerated by scripts/run_local_sweep.sh
# and scripts/run_slurm_sweep.sbatch). results/sample_run/ is the one
# committed, curated example dataset the analysis pipeline defaults to; it is
# explicitly un-ignored below.
results/*
!results/sample_run/
!results/sample_run/**
